el movimiento de moda de las feministas ha transformado el entorno laboral en estados unidos. los ejecutivos temen a las mujeres.

una nueva investigación realizada este año por la sociedad para la gestión de recursos humanos (shrm) en estados unidos confirma que casi un tercio de los 1.034 ejecutivos encuestados dijeron haber cambiado sus comportamientos a un nivel moderado
column2: grande o muy grande. y atención
column3: porque los jefes han hecho tres cuartos de lo mismo. el informe desvela que una cuarta parte de los 1022 gerentes también dijeron que habían cambiado sus comportamientos.

las denuncias de las mujeres en el entorno laboral que supuestamente han sido agredidas sexualmente se ha incrementado hasta un 83%. el 15% de trabajadores del estudio del shrm piensa que el #metoo ha evocado un ambiente de trabajo hostil para ambos géneros.

column1: el 30% de los gerentes hombres habría admitido que ""se sienten incómodos trabajando solos con una mujer"". un total de 32 estados americanos presentaron más de 125 leyes en este último año plagado de lemas feministas. no obstante

column1: 293050;instagram;2018-10-14 23:28:15;FALSE;"you know what the biggest lesson i’ve learnt is? that i’m much stronger than i think i am. when i think of the things i survived
column2: i’m in love with the woman i’ve become. sometimes we don’t realize it

column1: i’ve experienced happy times and sad times. i thought hard before sharing this
column2: but i’ve also experienced awful trauma. trauma so bad i blocked it out for 1 1/2years. i didn’t accept it for what it was. the thing with a deep wound is that it’ll keep hurting and getting worse if you ignore it. but when someone you truly trusted violates and hurts you in a way you always prayed would never happen to you
column3: eventho you said no... what do you do? it wasn’t just your body that was hurt
column4: the worse damage was done to your mind. so for me
column5: i blocked everything out and never thought about it again for a long time.

column1: what i didn’t realize was that after 1 1/2 years
column2: a wound that size was just gathering infection the whole time. my trust and insecurity levels got really bad and my confidence and love for myself was almost nonexistent. i put so much faith in my current boyfriend as one of the “good guys” that i’d break if he said a simple word that affected me. it brought back the #anxiety and #depression i thought i got rid of
column3: 20x worse. i didn’t even realize when things started getting so bad and i swear i never realized the root cause. that something left unattended for so long could turn my whole life upside down.

column1: so of course i had to stop ignoring it. i open my mind to what really happened and let me tell you
column2: it’s been a rollercoaster. i cried for 3 weeks straight
column3: day and night. it was like it happened yesterday. but i did seek therapy and i pray about it constantly. as you can imagine
column4: a wound that bad will take a while to heal but i can honestly say i’m doing better
column6: i’m healing. i’m not angry. yes it’s still a painful part of my past
column8: my past. i’m stronger and i won’t let this control me or ruin my life anymore. i’ll still win.

column4: just about everywhere...because of how patriarchy is deeply entrenched in our societies and selves.

column1: while movements like #metoo  have definitely worked to the effect of starting a dialogue about issues like consent
column3: let us not let this pass as yet another issue that we discuss amidst our circles at events or on social-media and then forget about it. patriarchy is reflected in all these things and more.

column1: and as i was discussing with a few friends over the past few days
column2: to everyone who's now found the courage to voice their stories as a way of catharsis
column3: because of the movement....totally respect your choice but
column4: please don't ever be afraid and continue speaking-up. you are your own 'movement'. honestly
column7: no friendship or alliance as much as your own self-respect. so there really is no point of suffering in silence and not reporting cases of violence and misconduct. one's gotta do what one's gotta do and the only option is being brave and unafraid!

column2: it's also upon all of us to not trivialise and treat instances of assault as ""things like these keep happening""
column3: constantly putting the blame on women
column4: judging women for the clothes they wear/things they say and part-taking in this whole 'circle of silence' which then necessitates the need for a hashtag like #metoo. let's fight sexism and patriarchy

column1: 293167;instagram;2018-10-14 22:00:05;FALSE;"@gilliana’s character stella gibson says it so well in this episode of #thefall. silence is not consent. @thealmontefilms talks about the forgotten ‘freeze’ defense mechanism besides fight or flight in one of his videos as well. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . i’m a survivor of sexual assault. i froze. i was a child and he was bigger and stronger than me. when i spoke up it was because flashbacks were making me depressed
column2: and suicidal. i was dying to get the secret out of me. i started with just little whispers
column5: and then my parents. when my parents denied it and told me not to tell anyone or press charges they chose to protect my abuser and thought that they could silence me. instead i got angry. i told anyone who would listen
column7: in person. when people told me to quiet down and just play nice i got angry. i mourned the loss of my parental support and i got help for myself at just 17 against the wishes of my parents. therapy heals me to this day. i survived. i’ve spoken at universities
column9: i’ve even been emmy nominated! i feel stronger because i had my voice
column10: my roar. i’ve had people share stories of survival that they’ve never told anyone else. i’ve created a safe place in myself. i can’t press charges because of the statute of limitations in ny but my roar keeps him away. my roar tells others that sexual assault will not be ignored. i can use my voice to connect and to heal and create a community of folks who are maybe uncovering their story after years of denial or outside pressure to keep quiet. whether you chose fight
column11: flight or freeze. it kept you safe. now
column14: you’re not alone. send us your roar! 🔊bgr

column1: i will hold you accountable for your actions.
i will set healthy boundaries that feels right for me.
i will take care of my own drama.
i will forever walk away from toxic relationships.
i will raise my voice when i see & experience injustice.
i will let my fire burn within my heart
column2: for no one to put my light out or make it burn any less bright.

column1: i will not shrink for you.
i will not change what is most holy about me.
i will not smile unless i want to.
i will not give you any fake approval.
if it’s “nice” you want then walk away. i will give you what’s real.
this does not mean i don’t love you.
or that i am not a being of love. .
all these things are how divine unconditional love moves through me. this is how i love you. this is how i love myself.

column3: fake or something you can walk all over.

column2: even though his conviction was based on something outside of that protest? it certainly appears that way
column4: that argument grew louder when prosecutors in new york announced they were dropping portions of the criminal charges against disgraced movie mogul harvey weinstein. the tossed charge — count six — involves allegations made by one of the three accusers in the case
column6: who was among the first women to publicly accuse the disgraced movie mogul of sexual assault

column1: in an exposé published in the new yorker a year ago
column2: evans accused weinstein of forcing her to perform oral sex when they met alone in his tribeca office in 2004 to discuss her fledgling acting career.at the time
column3: evans was a 21-year-old college student. assistant district attorney joan illuzzi-orbon told the judge this week that prosecutors wouldn’t oppose dismissal of the count in the case involving evans.weinstein’s lawyer
column5: told the judge he believed evans had lied to the grand jury. he also said he believed a police detective had corruptly tried to influence the case by keeping a witness from testifying about her misstatements.“the integrity of these proceedings has been compromised
column6: ” he said. weinstein’s attorneys and prosecutors had been wrangling over the part of the indictment concerning evans’ allegations over the last few weeks in closed-door meetings and sealed court papers
column9: about 90-minutes from the norristown courthouse where cosby was convicted in april on three counts of aggravated indecent assault
column10: some individuals approached by nnpa newswire said they believe the entire weinstein case will ultimately be tossed.

column1: 293198;instagram;2018-10-14 21:20:59;FALSE;"i spent the weekend at a course learning a new procedure that promises to bring about an improvement for people suffering in chronic pain due to complex regional pain syndrome
column4: and lumbar radiculopathy.  lots of thoughts passed through my head.

column2: it's our job to maintain our skill set and stay up to speed with the latest treatments being offered. with technology advancing so quickly
column3: we owe it to our patients to keep up to date on the best treatment options available for them. you never know it all and you can never learn enough. there's always room to improve your craft. truly be the best you can because your brain and intelligence are gifts from above. don't waste them.

column1: it was wonderful connecting with old colleagues and new ones. the older ones
column3: remind you why you got into medicine. their passion is contagious and their experience is priceless. learn from them. soak it up like a sponge. the newer ones remind you of where you started and how far you've come. you then become a source of inspiration to them and positive cycle of influence perpetuates. it makes you feel good inside 😊

column6: desi woman who does what i do. that makes me a bada$$ and i hope inspire more girls like me to do whatever it is they set their minds to.

column1: 293203;instagram;2018-10-14 21:23:52;FALSE;"there was a time in history where a witch was an honored member of society. she was respected for her unique connection to the unseen
column3: the spiritual world and was called upon to help the community during difficult times. she was the tribe's healer
column5: therapist and religious leader. she usually lived on the outskirts of town (right in nature) so she could keep her connection to the spiritual world strong. her gift was passed on from mother to daughter for millennia. to be called a witch was a badge of honor.

column1: then somewhere around the time of the christian colonization period throughout europe it was no longer lawful for the locals to seek spiritual guidance from their local witch. only a priest of the christian religion could do offer that. but many communities resisted this new culture.
that is when the greatest pr campaign and holocaust against women began. women in their twenties and thirties who were unmarried
column2: independent and had healing knowledge were targeted
column3: persecuted and killed. they were labeled as 'hags'
column4: 'servants of satan' and 'demons'. they were thrown off cliffs to see if they could fly or drowned in vats to see if they would survive.

column2: 000 women were executed for suspected witchcraft. all because god would never give women the power of healing
column3: so it must be the devil's works. its so sad and one of the biggest reasons i feel it is so important to take back the word witch for ourselves and reclaim our power!

column1: and at day 139 of saying no more to binge eating and soothing this soul with food - i feel powerful. 🦁

column2: i’ve not spoken about what simmers underneath this mechanism of eating that i turned to 💛

column1: but underneath it all sits a big story. that i’m not just unpacking for myself… but one i’m peeling the layers back for others.

column2: pirouette and sway as the 'pain' moves through me… 🌪 and other times i grapple
column4: fall down and graze my knees as it comes up at me.

column1: when you surrender to a coping mechanism
column2: an addiction and when you commit to seeing it through until it’s very end - you realise that when you don’t act on the impulse
column3: it is actually the biggest doorway to freedom of suffering
column4: and the biggest doorway to love. 🙌

column1: not eating gave me a purpose
column2: something to focus on. bulimia and bingeing gave me relief for the relentless attempt to run from the frightening reality of what was going on

column1: now where i stand tall at day 139 i’ve arrived at a place where i realise that being quiet - is unbearable.
that opening the heart to being vulnerable

column2: i want to thank you binge for keeping me safe when you did
column3: and thank you for continuing to send me the impulse to ‘lose’ myself again
column4: showing me the fire that’s really waiting to be lit underneath.

column1: i’m feeling that readiness to stand up for others who need to see that light
column2: who need a voice to break their silence and to turn the pain and suffering into armor and weapons - so we can face off the wolves who go out there to rip us apart limb

column1: inside this girl - there is a light that never goes out. that light is burning brightly inside of you
i’m not going to abandon you.
big love to you all! xoxo 👊

column1: 293381;instagram;2018-10-14 19:17:38;FALSE;"“here is to raising boys who become men who are compassionate—to themselves and others.
here is to raising boys who become men who are able to name and healthily be with their feelings.
here is to raising boys who become men who regard life—in all its forms.
here is to raising boys who become men who redefine what “power” means.
here is to raising boys who become men who acknowledge and balance the masculine and feminine in themselves and encourage this healthy balance in our culture.
here is to raising boys who become men who can ask for help and who believe that being vulnerable is an act of bravery and strength.”-lisa mccrohan 💙

cosas a tener en cuenta sobre la salud mental: 🍃habla si lo necesitas. aunque te asuste
column2: lo agradecerás en un futuro. 🍃además de compartir la misma importancia
column3: la salud mental y física están fuertemente relacionadas. acuérdate de beber agua
column5: hacer ejercicio/ir a dar una vuelta y dormir una cantidad apropiada de horas cada día. mantener una buena higiene personal también te ayuda a sentirte ""mentalmente limpix"". 🍃habla en nombre de la gente que tiene enfermedades mentales. muestra tu apoyo y disposición a escuchar. no les culpes por su enfermedad. ayúdales de la mejor forma que puedas
column6: lo cual está relacionado con el próximo punto... 🍃antes de tratar de ayudar a alguien
column7: cuida de ti mismx. no puedes ayudar a levantarse a alguien si tú mismx estás hundido. os será de poca ayuda a los dos. levántate tú primero. 🍃ayuda a eliminar el estigma. edúcate sobre salud y enfermedad mental. interviene si alguien está siendo irrespetuoso o compartiendo información falsa sobre las enfermedades mentales. 🍃mantén el contacto con tus amigos. puede que no sea ""divertido"" escribir a ese amigx que siempre parece estar triste
column8: pero podrías alegrarle el día. pregúntale cómo se siente
column9: es probable que esté buscando alguien con quien desahogarse. ve más allá del ""estoy bien"". quizá mándale algo que sabes que le hará sonreír. recuérdale que no es una molestia. 🍃toma pausas. estamos acostumbrados a recibir estímulos constantemente y puede ser muy abrumador. tómate un día lejos del trabajo y los estudios
column10: o un día sin redes sociales. toma aire fresco

column1: 293441;instagram;2018-10-14 18:22:21;FALSE;"ikväll var jag med i ett extrasänt program i @expressentv om betydelsen av #metoo.
en lång resa har startat där män behöver börja med sig själva för att sexuellt våld ska stoppas. män behöver ta sitt egenansvar för att inhämta samtycke i alla mellanmänskliga relationer.

column2: 2013 startade fatta och 2017 kom metoo. metoo är en världsomspännande revolution för kvinnors mänskliga rättigheter och i de flesta länder pratar man nu om behovet av frihet från rädsla för mäns sexuella våld.

column1: vad händer nu? rättsväsendet måste göra sitt jobb och tillämpa samtyckeslagen. och alla elever måste ha tillgång till sex och samtyckesundervisning. samtycke ska vara ett självklart begrepp i läroplanen. - vi borde ha kommit längre. i media pratar vi  fortfarande om uthängningars vara eller icke vara. det är dags att vi börjar agera. - tjejer

column1: 293498;instagram;2018-10-14 17:36:02;FALSE;"families experience different emotions at different times in response to the discovery that a member of their family has been sexually abused by another family member. but families cannot protect the rights and safety of all the children of the family while keeping the sexual abuse secret or by defending the abuser. no matter what the consequences are for the sexual abuser we must always choose to protect children. the secrecy of incest in my family ran for 5 generations. secrecy
column2: lies and denial destroyed many people in my family. i was the first person of the many sexual abuse survivors in my family to come forward with the sexual abuse to the police and publicly.

column1: 💥i’ve been noticing some of you getting riled up about this post #metoo climate we’re living in.

🔗i’ve heard fears of false accusations. i’ve heard concerns about how to behave naturally with women without worrying about crossing some line. 🥊and i hear that things are changing and that sometimes change is scary…
✊🏼especially when it feels to us like we’re losing ground 🕳and giving up our power.

column2: i just want to make one thing absolutely clear. any form of power that is lost when someone else becomes empowered is not our true power. power that can be lost by making room for someone else to rise... that is false power. rather than feeling victimized by the changes we’re seeing in the male/female dynamic these days
column3: i would love to see men looking at these changes as an opportunity to make an inquiry into what true empowerment would mean in this new paradigm.

column1: 293505;instagram;2018-10-14 17:38:18;FALSE;"as a survivor of dv this is one of the most common misconceptions that i have had to fight both inside of myself & to others.
until i was in an abusive relationship i never understood why they ""didn't just leave
column2: either. now i know better & that it is never that easy. even at the end
column3: when i started wanting to leave i felt so small
column5: and unsure of how to get out of the situation...

column1: my mother & sister saw the signs though & they never stopped trying. if it weren't for their support
column3: and the strength that their support gave me
column4: i'm honestly not sure where i would be today. ❤❤❤ i'll be forever greatful to them & to my father & step-parents for their unwavering support through this ordeal & the difficult court proceedings that followed it.

column2: i'm still far from where i want to be but i can genuinely say that i'm working on myself & with the help of family
column4: and doctors—i'm starting to truly heal myself and to move forward. 💗💗 but without that network of support i'd likely still be stagnant & drowning inside of myself. so please #seethesigns & look out for your loved ones. they may act defensive
column5: like they don't need your help but believe me—they do

at a company i used to work for
column2: a senior person put time on my calendar to “catch up”
column3: despite that our work did not require us to interact

column2: he eventually said: “i’ve been meaning to ask you...how do you have such nice legs?”

column1: it is unclear how i responded
column2: because i’m pretty sure i just blacked out from awkwardness from being asked this 1. at work 2. during my first month at this company 3. in a room alone with this man who was 4. 30+ years older than me

column1: when i ultimately left the company (for unrelated reasons)
column2: he called me into his office and asked me why i was leaving. before letting me answer
column3: he said: “if you decide to enter miss america

column1: all of this while another manager at the company told me my work dresses were too short and made male counterparts uncomfortable 😑
getting engaged to my life partner of 8 years was a joy and being married has been the same
some of you know i fell *slightly* ill (aka we called an ambulance) at our wedding
i spent a large portion of the night in the bathroom. max sat by my side and took care of me as he enjoyed his dinner on the floor 😂
here is to commemorating a movement that undoubtedly shed light on an important issue and to finding the people who help us through it
other honorable mentions go out to:
my brother @callme_will who played this song on the piano as i walked down the aisle
some kid named @davidcalello for the drone footage

293594;instagram;2018-10-14 17:03:01;FALSE;yesterday i came across an instagram post written by a clown called @rachel.cargle - cargle is an academic and lecturer with a big following on social media
column2: and she recently wrote about how vegans have no right to criticize nonvegans. she talked about food deserts
column3: migrant workers and all that tired
column4: old shit which clowns like her love to regurgitate as though they've somehow found a groundbreaking argument which completely “debunks” veganism. her previous entry on instagram was a photo of the breakfast she got while staying in a hotel somewhere (the hotel was clearly not the cheap kind
column5: by the way). the breakfast included pig flesh. i'm sure she'd be happy to know that her posts have truly inspired me. they've inspired me to write a message to cargle and all other clowns like her: you're not fooling anybody.

column2: everyone knows that you didn't eat that piece of flesh for breakfast because you're worried about the poor; you ate it because you like the way flesh tastes when it's cooked and seasoned. that's what this comes down to. you inflict violence upon vulnerable beings for no better reason than your fucking palate pleasure
column3: while you're on tour giving talks about oppression and discrimination. you are the epitome of hypocrisy. more than that
column4: you are the epitome of intellectual dishonesty. you don't care about the people whose struggles you use as an excuse for your choice to enslave animals. if you did
column5: you wouldn't be using those people and their struggles as a way to make you seem like a less shitty person.

column3: let me clarify: when i say you're not fooling anybody
column4: that includes the clowns who share your anti-vegan posts. they don't believe that shit either. those “veganism isn't' cruelty-free” articles do not go viral because people care about migrant workers. most people don't give a fuck about the rights of workers. anti-vegan posts go viral for one reason
column5: and one reason only: they tell people what they wanna hear. people want to be told that vegans don't have the moral high ground. that way

column2: inspiring women & courageous men at #wowexeter for exeter's women of the world festival. i find these gatherings so nourishing ❤️ women need spaces like these where safety & inclusivity are brought consciously into the room: where our real & our joy can be welcomed side by side - not to be judged
column5: but to be witnessed & heard by others. these are the spaces we need to help us navigate the human experience through the many social
column6: political & environmental challenges we face. thank you all at @wowexeter x

column1: my h i g h l i g h t s ...

_don’t just stand there! i learnt about the various direct & indirect ways we can safely intervene as active bystanders to protect people (women & anyone) subject to inappropriate behaviour. safe techniques range from how to safely intervene in a physical attack
column2: to lighter situations such as simply choosing not to laugh or creating a distraction when we witness verbal humiliation/abuse. i feel like this session was a start in equipping me with safe invention tools that i can feel comfortable using. i’ve come away feeling how much we need to work as a collective to support those suffering as a result of sexist
column3: racist or prejudiced perpetrators to send the message that it is not ok & it will not be normalised.

column1: _did you know that devon & cornwall police recognise misogynist behaviour in public spaces as a hate crime? nottingham police do the same thing = a big step towards making everyday life safer for women & girls.

column2: open conversation around motherhood & childfree choice. so grateful for real stories & experiences around this. motherhood is not all love 'n’ light & cute photos ~ mothers are easily isolated & need support from the childfree tribe.

column1: _ we are the grandchildren of the witches you didn’t burn! & we need witches & ecofeminists more than ever. women & men can rebalance the masculine (active) & feminine (receptive) principles within themselves to make change in their everyday lives. reconnect with the land to bring conscious ritual & deep reverence back into our lives - listen & the land will guide you. ↓ continued ↓";;en;#wowexeter;@wowexeter;;;;0;;pellarandpollen;H a y l e y;;0;False;7;0;0;39;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/c0da9f0ca3b9102f5ebf3694a811178b/5D1304DA/t51.2885-15/e35/42524055_167146387554846_8693501057524246847_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"wow

column2: inspiring women & courageous men at #wowexeter for exeter's women of the world festival. i find these gatherings so nourishing ❤️ women need spaces like these where safety & inclusivity are brought consciously into the room: where our real & our joy can be welcomed side by side - not to be judged
column5: but to be witnessed & heard by others. these are the spaces we need to help us navigate the human experience through the many social
column6: political & environmental challenges we face. thank you all at @wowexeter x

_don’t just stand there! i learnt about the various direct & indirect ways we can safely intervene as active bystanders to protect people (women & anyone) subject to inappropriate behaviour. safe techniques range from how to safely intervene in a physical attack
column2: to lighter situations such as simply choosing not to laugh or creating a distraction when we witness verbal humiliation/abuse. i feel like this session was a start in equipping me with safe invention tools that i can feel comfortable using. i’ve come away feeling how much we need to work as a collective to support those suffering as a result of sexist
column3: racist or prejudiced perpetrators to send the message that it is not ok & it will not be normalised.

column1: 293724;instagram;2018-10-14 15:47:13;FALSE;"till now you must have read many #metoo stories on social media and most of them must be of someone famous. i
column2: am not famous. yet here i am to share my story.

column1: it was a tuesday. i was in seventh grade and i had my dance classes in the evening. i came back from school when mom told me that an uncle (my grandpa's cousin) was visiting us in the evening. he used to be the favourite among kids. so even i liked him a lot. when he arrived everything was fine. but now it was time for my dance classes and he was leaving at night. so by the time i come back from my dance classes
column2: it would have been time for him to leave. so i request mom that i didn't want to go that day. she agreed but said i had to rehearse at home and show him my dance. i was rejoiced. i clearly don't remember why but mom had to go out for some reason. so she left.

column1: we have a swing in the middle of our living room. i was sitting on it and he was on the sofa. he asked me to switch on the tv. i stood up
column2: got the remote and switched the tv on. as i was about to sit on the swing when he said that come sit besides me. i sat and then he touched me. touched me in a way that the memory of it still makes me shudder. he touched and kissed me at places on my body. i tried to ran but he was not letting me. i was screaming but the doors were closed. somehow i managed to get away and ran out of the house. some kids were playing on the terrace so i went to them. and sat on the terrace until mom came. mom had brought pineapple. both of us went in the house. i don't remember much from here but i told mom i want to tell her something while she was making pineapple juice. she handed me a glass and said go give this glass to him then come and we'll talk. i said no and told her to come to the washroom. i told her everything and then i was said not to come out of my room. the pineapple juice was served. dad came home and went to drop him to the railway station. i was put to sleep.

column1: 293780;instagram;2018-10-14 14:57:45;FALSE;the #metoo movement has been making a positive impact in empowering individuals to speak out about sexual harassment and assault. more and more men and women all over the world 🌎 are coming forward to speak up and it's changing the landscape of #employmentlaw for the better. in california ab1825 requires that employers with 50 or more employees provide training on preventing harassment
column4: with very specific requirements to employees every 2 years. with the recent spotlight on this important topic
column5: a new bill from the california state senate will require this same training for employers with 5 employees beginning in january
column6: 2020. employers should take the time now to ensure they are prepared by updating policies and communicating with them that their work environment is a safe place to report these acts. if you need any assistance in this area feel free to contact humanity hr consulting. #hrpartners #hrconsultants #womensbusiness #humansfirst;;en;#metoo

column1: 🌺 just as both are equally important
column2: mental and physical well-being are strongly connected. remember to drink water
column4: do some exercise/go for a walk and get a proper amount of sleep. keeping a good hygiene helps you feel 'mentally clean'. 🌺 speak up for people with mental illnesses. show support and listen to them. don't blame them for their illness. help them the best way you can
column5: which is related to the next point...

column1: 🌺 before trying to help someone out
column2: take care of yourself. you can't lift others properly if you're on the ground. it will be of little help to neither of you. raise yourself first. 🌺help end the stigma. educate yourself about mental illness and mental health. step in if someone is being disrespectful or sharing incorrect information about mental illnesses. 🌺check in on your friends. it may not be 'fun' to write to that friend who always seems sad
column3: but it could brighten their day. ask how they're feeling
column4: they're probably looking forward to venting. go beyond the ""i am fine"". maybe send them something you know will make them smile. remind them they are not a burden. 🌺 take breaks. we are used to always receiving stimuli and it can be so very overwhelming. take a day off from work/studying
column5: a day off social media. get some fresh air
column6: do something you love even if you're not good at it.

293928;instagram;2018-10-14 13:28:45;FALSE;indreshkumarofficial#metoo campaign पर आदरणीय इन्द्रेश कुमार जी का संदेश :-- •भारत नारी को सम्मान और सुरक्षा करने वाला देश है
column3: बहन और बेटी के रूप में देखा जाता है। • #metoo के अंतर्गत जो भी घटनाएं हुई थी वो ज्यादातर कांग्रेस (upa) की सरकार के दौरान घटित हुई। क्या इन नारियों को काँग्रेस के राज में इंसाफ पाने का भरोसा नही था? •पीड़ित नारियों
column5: को इतनी देर तक यह अत्याचार छुपाना नही चाहिए था और ऐसी घटनाओं को पुलिस और न्यायपालिका में रिपोर्ट करना चाहिए था। •दशकों से तीन तलाक़ पीड़ित मुस्लिम महिलाओं को वर्तमान सरकार ने ही कानून बना कर न्याय दिलाने का प्रयास किया है। •मेरी पीड़ित महिलाओं से ये अपील है कि वे लंबा अत्याचार न सहें
column6: जल्द से जल्द कानून की मदद लें । •काँग्रेस सरकार ने अपने शासनकाल में मीडिया का दुरूपयोग करके भगवा-आतंकवाद के नाम पर कई निर्दोषों पर अन्याय और अत्याचार किये। मुझे भी इन झूठे आरोपों में फसाने का प्रयास किया गया
column7: लेकिन अंततः सत्य जीता और सभी आरोप झूठे साबित हुए। • मेरी मीडिया से यह अपील है कि विपक्ष द्वारा बनाए गए झूठे ट्रैप में दोबारा ना फसे और कांग्रेस सरकार को भगवा आंतकवाद के नाम में किए गए अत्याचार के लिए पूरे राष्ट्र से माफी मांगनी चाहिए। • सरकार से अपील है कि #metoo कैंपेन के तहत जिन पर भी आरोप लगे हैं
column8: उनकी निष्पक्ष जांच की जाए और अगर आरोप सिद्ध होते हैं तो उन्हें उचित से उचित सज़ा दी जाए ताकि भारत में महिलाओं का सम्मान और गरिमा स्थापित की जा सके। सरकार से यह अपील है कि जिस तरह से उसने कानून बना कर 3 तलाक रूपी अत्याचार से 8.5 करोड़ मुस्लिम महिलाओं को मुक्ति दी है उसी तरह से अच्छी कानूनी प्रक्रिया से #metoo कैंपेन के तहत सामने आ रही लोगों को उचित न्याय दिलवाने के हर प्रयास करें ।

column1: • जो लोग यह कह रहे हैं कि नारी का वर्षों- वर्षों तक अपने शोषण को छुपा कर रखना उचित है वे गलत है और वे नारी के सम्मान के प्रतीक नहीं बल्कि नारी को दबाने और उनका शोषण करने के प्रतीक हैं। • जिन जिन लोगों पर #metoo कैंपेन के तहत आरोप लगे हैं उन्हें आगे आकर इन आरोपों का सामना करना चाहिए और राजनीतिक दलों को चाहिए कि इस संवेदनशील विषय पर राजनीति ना करें। • भारत आदिकाल से नारी का सम्मान करने वाला देश है। यहां नारी को ईश्वर के रूप में पूजा जाता है। आओ हम सब मिलकर एक बार पुनः नारी सम्मान और सुरक्षा को स्थापित करें और मेरी माँ

column8: बहन और बेटी के रूप में देखा जाता है। • #metoo के अंतर्गत जो भी घटनाएं हुई थी वो ज्यादातर कांग्रेस (upa) की सरकार के दौरान घटित हुई। क्या इन नारियों को काँग्रेस के राज में इंसाफ पाने का भरोसा नही था? •पीड़ित नारियों
column10: को इतनी देर तक यह अत्याचार छुपाना नही चाहिए था और ऐसी घटनाओं को पुलिस और न्यायपालिका में रिपोर्ट करना चाहिए था। •दशकों से तीन तलाक़ पीड़ित मुस्लिम महिलाओं को वर्तमान सरकार ने ही कानून बना कर न्याय दिलाने का प्रयास किया है। •मेरी पीड़ित महिलाओं से ये अपील है कि वे लंबा अत्याचार न सहें
column11: जल्द से जल्द कानून की मदद लें । •काँग्रेस सरकार ने अपने शासनकाल में मीडिया का दुरूपयोग करके भगवा-आतंकवाद के नाम पर कई निर्दोषों पर अन्याय और अत्याचार किये। मुझे भी इन झूठे आरोपों में फसाने का प्रयास किया गया
column12: लेकिन अंततः सत्य जीता और सभी आरोप झूठे साबित हुए। • मेरी मीडिया से यह अपील है कि विपक्ष द्वारा बनाए गए झूठे ट्रैप में दोबारा ना फसे और कांग्रेस सरकार को भगवा आंतकवाद के नाम में किए गए अत्याचार के लिए पूरे राष्ट्र से माफी मांगनी चाहिए। • सरकार से अपील है कि #metoo कैंपेन के तहत जिन पर भी आरोप लगे हैं
column13: उनकी निष्पक्ष जांच की जाए और अगर आरोप सिद्ध होते हैं तो उन्हें उचित से उचित सज़ा दी जाए ताकि भारत में महिलाओं का सम्मान और गरिमा स्थापित की जा सके। सरकार से यह अपील है कि जिस तरह से उसने कानून बना कर 3 तलाक रूपी अत्याचार से 8.5 करोड़ मुस्लिम महिलाओं को मुक्ति दी है उसी तरह से अच्छी कानूनी प्रक्रिया से #metoo कैंपेन के तहत सामने आ रही लोगों को उचित न्याय दिलवाने के हर प्रयास करें ।

column958: उनकी निष्पक्ष जांच की जाए और अगर आरोप सिद्ध होते हैं तो उन्हें उचित से उचित सज़ा दी जाए ताकि भारत में महिलाओं का सम्मान और गरिमा स्थापित की जा सके। सरकार से यह अपील है कि जिस तरह से उसने कानून बना कर 3 तलाक रूपी अत्याचार से 8.5 करोड़ मुस्लिम महिलाओं को मुक्ति दी है उसी तरह से अच्छी कानूनी प्रक्रिया से कैंपेन के तहत सामने आ रही लोगों को उचित न्याय दिलवाने के हर प्रयास करें । • जो लोग यह कह रहे हैं कि नारी का वर्षों- वर्षों तक अपने शोषण को छुपा कर रखना उचित है वे गलत है और वे नारी के सम्मान के प्रतीक नहीं बल्कि नारी को दबाने और उनका शोषण करने के प्रतीक हैं। • जिन जिन लोगों पर कैंपेन के तहत आरोप लगे हैं उन्हें आगे आकर इन आरोपों का सामना करना चाहिए और राजनीतिक दलों को चाहिए कि इस संवेदनशील विषय पर राजनीति ना करें। • भारत आदिकाल से नारी का सम्मान करने वाला देश है। यहां नारी को ईश्वर के रूप में पूजा जाता है। आओ हम सब मिलकर एक बार पुनः नारी सम्मान और सुरक्षा को स्थापित करें और मेरी माँ
column959: बहन और बेटियों से एक बार फिर से यह अपील है कि वह अपने ऊपर हो रहे किसी भी अत्याचार को छुपाएं नही बल्कि इस के ख;indreshkumarofficial campaign पर आदरणीय इन्द्रेश कुमार जी का संदेश : -- •भारत नारी को सम्मान और सुरक्षा करने वाला देश है

वैसे सफलता और कामयाबी की ताली बजवानी है तो हाथ तो आपने भी दिया था देते है और देंगे ही तभी न कोई हाथ रखता है  या हाथ पर हाथ मारता है तभी न आपकी सफलता की तालियों की आवाज दूर तक सुनाई देता है जो आज सुनाई भी दे रहा है बहुत दूर तक अब आपकी आवाज जाने लगी है देखिए न उतने दिन पहले की ताली मुझे इतने जोड़ से सुनाई पड़ी है

आइये एक वास्तविक उदहारण से हम समझते है upsc ने अपने अंदर एक परिवर्तन पर विचार कर रही थी जिसमें था कि आपका चयन हो जाने के बाद आपको ias ips ies का चुनाव आपके ट्रेनिंग के समय स्किल कोर्स के आधार पर होगा लोगों की प्रतिक्रिया आई उसमें मैंने एक प्रतिक्रिया यहाँ रखता हूं जिसमें कहा जाता है कि यह तो अच्छा है हम कैसे भी चयन तो हो फिर वहां कुछ अपनी वैसी काबलियत दिखा कर प्रयास किया जाएगा मनपसंद चुनाव के लिए
यह बात एक जगह के लिए नही हर जगह कैसा उपयोग होता है सब जानते है
अब मैं यह भी नहीं कह रहा हूं कि ओ बंद चारदीवारी के अंदर तालाब की हलचल के कीचड़ में सब कमल पिंक ही होते है कुछ सफेद भी होता है मैं उस सफदे कमल पर बिल्कुल कुछ नही कह रहा हु
